  "instructions": [
    "Preheat grill to medium-high heat (around 375°F or 190°C).",
    "In a shallow dish, combine olive oil, cumin powder, garlic powder, salt, black pepper, and lime juice. Toss chicken wings in the marinade for at least 20 minutes.",
    "Remove from marinade and lightly dust with oregano powder.",
    "Place chicken wings on preheated grill skin side down. Cook until crispy and golden brown (around 8-10 minutes).",
    "Flip to the other side and cook another 5-7 minutes or until fully cooked through.",
    "Serve hot as a low-fat-friendly snack."
